														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4733686">
									

<p>A 'cliche' is a type of 'trope' that is so repetitive and overused, it's tedious and actually a little painful to read. I saw little to no cliches here, only tropes.</p>
<p>Tropes are necessary in keeping short stories short. We don't need to know where Bagel grew up and how he got into the business, all we need to start is 'gangster' and a tiny detail to make him unique. The author then takes it from there.</p>
<p>An even better author will also drop hints of a greater world with even more adventures. But this right here is the adventure we're reading about today. @Rounderhouse also did this by hinting about the Big Bad Guy's greater plans.</p>
<p>+1 all around.</p>

