					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lonlanglin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6517279); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6517279&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182917" alt="LonLangLin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6517279)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lonlanglin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6517279); return false;" >LonLangLin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1595083621 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Jul 2020 14:47</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4722878">
									

<p>This came out a bit long, unfortunately, but the following is my explanation as to why I gave this article a -1.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Show</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I'll start by clarifying that, when I read this page for the first time, I gave it a +1. That's because this is a good page - there's a good plot with a nice twist, all of the characters feel believable, and the setting and backstory contribute as well.</p>
<p>The reason I now changed my vote to a -1 is because, while I feel like this is a great contribution to the site, it's not one I feel should be in the format of an SCP article. SCPs are things the Foundation either contains or has contained, for an indefinite amount of time. This is why the articles have Containment Procedures right at the top - they're supposed to help Foundationers continue the potentially perpetual containment of the anomaly.</p>
<p>This article discusses a group of anomalous humans, which means the Foundation would've certainly had an interest in them, and would indeed have apprehended them as described in the article. The problem here is that, as far as I can tell, all of the events of this article take place within 2 days. The Foundation &quot;representative&quot; here mentions multiple times that the Foundation has no interest in indefinitely arresting these guys, and that they will be released into the regular justice system once the investigation is over.</p>
<p>This doesn't feel like something the Foundation would write an SCP document about. Honestly, it feels like it would've taken the Foundation a longer time to write this article than the amount of time these guys were in containment. In my opinion, this story would better fit into the world as a tale - an in-universe documentation of the investigation, perhaps. Unfortunately, this means that for now, I'm giving it a -1.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

